FBIS4-20074 "drweu080_o_94002" FBIS-WEU-94-080 Daily Report 25 Apr 1994 CYPRUS Government `Surprised' at Clinton's Optimism Government `Surprised' at Clinton's Optimism NC2504145694 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio Network in Greek 1400 GMT 25 Apr 94 NC2504145694 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio Network Greek BFN [Text] Government spokesman Ioannis Kasoulidhis was surprised at U.S. President Bill Clinton's optimism that the Turkish side will agree to the 21 March UN document. The spokesman also said that information regarding a change in the Turkish stance does not indicate this, and added that the government will await to confirm the Turkish position officially during its contact with the UN representative.
